<item>
            <title>[LU-13824] sanity test 230q fails with &apos;stripe hash crush,migrating != crush&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13824</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test_230q fails with &apos;stripe hash crush,migrating != crush&apos; for DNE/ZFS testing starting on 12 June 2020. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the recent failure at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4660852d-f9fc-4083-bf33-cecf0dcfdf7e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4660852d-f9fc-4083-bf33-cecf0dcfdf7e&lt;/a&gt;, the client test_log shows the test waiting for &#8216;lfs getdirstripe -H&#8217; to return crush, but gets &#8216;crush.migrating&#8217; and times out&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;CMD: trevis-66vm1.trevis.whamcloud.com /usr/bin/lfs getdirstripe -c /mnt/lustre/d230q.sanity
CMD: trevis-66vm1.trevis.whamcloud.com /usr/bin/lfs getdirstripe -H /mnt/lustre/d230q.sanity
Waiting 200s for &apos;crush&apos;
CMD: trevis-66vm1.trevis.whamcloud.com /usr/bin/lfs getdirstripe -H /mnt/lustre/d230q.sanity
&#8230;
CMD: trevis-66vm1.trevis.whamcloud.com /usr/bin/lfs getdirstripe -H /mnt/lustre/d230q.sanity
CMD: trevis-66vm1.trevis.whamcloud.com /usr/bin/lfs getdirstripe -H /mnt/lustre/d230q.sanity
Waiting 0s for &apos;crush&apos;
Update not seen after 200s: want &apos;crush&apos; got &apos;crush,migrating&apos;
 sanity test_230q: @@@@@@ FAIL: stripe hash crush,migrating != crush 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is nothing obviously wrong looking at the console and dmesg logs. &lt;/p&gt;


</description>
